net.novazero.lib.ikbus

Class CompoundIKBusMessageParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.novazero.lib.ikbus.CompoundIKBusMessageParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IKBusMessageParser

    public class CompoundIKBusMessageParser
extends Object
implements IKBusMessageParser
    An I/K-bus message parser that is composed of a set of of other parsers. When this parser is asked to parse an I/K-bus message from a given packet it simply iterates over its set of parsers and asks each parser to parse the message. Once a parser returns a non-null value, then that value will be returned by the compound message parser.
    Author:
    Daan Scheerens

        public IKBusMessage parseMessage(IKBusPacket packet)
                          throws IKBusMessageParseException
        Attempts to parse the I/K-bus message that is represented by the given packet.
        Specified by:
        parseMessage in interface IKBusMessageParser
        Parameters:
        packet - The I/K-bus packet that is to be parsed.
        Returns:
        An IKBusMessage message if the given packet was parsed successfully or null if the packet was not recognized/supported by the parser.
        Throws:
        IKBusMessageParseException - If an error occurs while parsing a recognized packet. This exception will not be thrown if the parser does not recognize the packet. In that case this method will return null.
